our grand daughter sleeps all day and is awake on and off all night she is days old and during the day she takes a whole oz bottle but during the night she wakes almost hourly feeds a little then goes back to sleep they have tried tickling her feet changing her to wake her but nothing works as you can imagine they are both shattered and wondered if there is anyway they can turn this upside down baby back the right way i to have a new born who is seven days old i belive in starting their routine right at the beginning it worked with my other two children and it still remains their routine now i bath them and have a little play with them then they are dryed and put in their night time clothes and given a feed it is then bedtime they have all been put in their cots awake so they can learn to fall asleep on their own this has been done around o clock at night so they recognise their bedtime i would try waking your granddaughter to prepare her for her bath etc i appriciate its not how everyone would do it but its worked for me Sleep Insomnia The Amber Spyglass Daylight saving time Breastfeeding Dream Urinary incontinence The Lion, the Witch and the Wardrobe Narcolepsy Characters of The Sandman Garfield Sleep debt Hansel und Gretel USS Abbot (DD-629) Canonical hours Diazepam Freddy's Dead: The Final Nightmare Apollo 8 Seiken Densetsu 3 Spirit rover timeline for 2004 March Infant Sin City Days of our Lives Lost At Sea (Care Bears) Knots Landing Sumo Ayyavazhi mythology Milton H. Erickson Lucid dreaming Conker's Bad Fur Day Bedwetting Delayed sleep phase syndrome Care Bears Wild at Heart (Buffy episode) The Legend of Zelda: Majora's Mask characters Sento Opportunity rover timeline for 2004 March Mattress Shaggy dog story Odyssey Opportunity rover timeline for 2004 February Avenue Q The Shining (film) Out-of-body experience Diaper Doctor Who (Enemy Within) Finnegans Wake Futurama (TV series - season 5) A Day in the Life Parsifal Harry Potter and the Prisoner of Azkaban Aeria